        <tr> 
          <td width="30">&nbsp;</td>
          <td width="405" class="texte">
FULL TIME POSITION Bordeaux, France<BR><BR>Working under the Operations Manager, you will participate in the administration of our client/server platform, a platform which lies at the very heart of our activity (downloadable games service for mobile phones). <BR><BR><BR>PRINCIPLE DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES<BR><BR> You will integrate onto the servers, all the software developed by our R&D teams<BR> You will operate and supervise our production servers in order to obtain information regarding the performance of our platform <BR> You provide technical support to the Test & Validation teams<BR> You will take care of the configuration of all new clients onto our platform as part of a new project we are currently undertaking<BR> You will write the configuration and installation documentation (in English)<BR> You will work in close collaboration with the Quality and R&D teams as well as working closely with our clients (operators and handset manufacturers)<BR><BR><BR>EDUCATION, EXPERIENCE AND SKILLS REQUIRED<BR><BR> You have a degree (Bachelors equivalent) in Computer Science <BR> You have experience of the UNIX operating system as well as development in SHELL and PERL<BR> Some knowledge of Java programming would be a definite advantage<BR> You are organised, methodical and rigorous in your work<BR> You are proactive and at ease in environments subject to much change <BR><BR>If you are a flexible, proactive individual and you are eager to participate in the growth of a highly international company, then please send us your CV.<BR><BR>We feel it is very important to help develop the skills of all our employees.  Thus, in order to help you along your career path, we do our best to maximize the possibility of internal promotion.<BR><BR>Do not forget to mention the reference OP0503SAT/IF <BR><BR>
